Alright, I'm awake now. It's safe to post.
I think.

So today I got screwed out of going to Steelers Training Camp - my ONLY CHANCE to go this year - because of a misunderstanding with the scheduling at work. I'm seriously mad. Like, I work my own shifts and take shifts for other people to help them and the store out (as is the case with my shift tonight) aaaaand I have to miss the one chance I had to go to Training Camp.
If tonight is anything like last night was, I'm really gonna be upset.

Anywayyy...I work tonight, have band camp all day tomorrow, and then work again tomorrow night. Tuesday is my day. Tuesday I leave to go see Jimmy. Tuesday will be magical. I'm not sure actually if I should hold off and leave on Wednesday due to the fact that Jimmy closes at his other sbux on Tuesday night, but I can't exactly work that out with him right now being that he's out of cell phone range.

So basically I've spent the day sitting around by myself watching movies, working out, and having random dance parties.
Fun, fun.

Guess I'm gonna go do some more nothing before it's work time. =)

amourtoujours, kait michelle

Gawshhh I am sooo tired.

Starbucks was absolutely insane tonight. Thanks to good ol' Richland Community Days celebrate our 175th anniversary extravaganza, we were crawling with little children demanding frappuccinos. It took us an hour to close. And I was closing with Tara.
If you worked at Starbucks, you would understand the impact of that fact.

It might be a little more acceptable that I'm tired and sore and cranky if I could talk to Jimmy, but alas, he is on mini-vacation with his family & some friends and it happens to be out of cell phone range. Blah. I feel weird and cut-off from him when I don't get to talk to him at night before I fall asleep. That's our thing:  the 2 AM phone calls of sleepy kids in love.

I want this year to be perfect. I don't quite know what perfect means, but I just want it to be everything that I've been patiently waiting for these past three months. This summer absolutely flew in the grand scheme of things, but it still didn't go fast enough in other ways. I don't even know what I mean anymore. SLEEP, KAIT!

Ok for real. I'm going to read more of The Vampire Lestat and get some serious sleep before I have to turn around and do this closing thing again tomorrow night.

I'll post again when I'm coherent. =)

amourtoujours, kait michelle

I swear, the fewer days there are before I get to see Jimmy, the harder it is. It's been a month since I've physically seen him and held him and kissed him and I'm going crazy. I, like anyone else, enjoy time to myself. I love to watch Friends and hang out w/ my sister & curl up and read a good book...but when it comes down to it, I would so much rather be with Jimmy. That is SO unique to this relationship, for me. In the past, I loved being with the person I was dating, but there were just some times when I really wanted to be alone. It's amazing how not sick I am of Jimmy. It's amazing how I can spend every waking moment with him and be completely and utterly happy. Blissfully happy. I think this is how it's supposed to be.

I'm totally against the whole wishing away days of summer idea, but we're already experiencing autumn-like weather in good ol' Jtown and the changing of the seasons will bring my baby back to me. I'm excited/anxious for school to start. UPJ will be new for me, but I'm ready. I'm ready to put my heart into it and work as much as I can at Starbucks and just be really proud of myself. I have Jimmy and he has me and we're gonna do the damn thing. For real.

As I'm sure I've mentioned a million times before, I've never had a one year anniversary, thus August 21, 2008 shall be a momentous day in the life of Kait. I'm super excited to reach this milestone with Jimmy. I know it probably won't change anything in our relationship whatsoever, but it's just so exciting. It's gonna be a day all about us. No one else. And I don't care what we do. At all. As long as I'm with him I will be so happy. So happy. I'm practically chomping at the bit to give him his anniversary present(s). I love making him happy and I hope he likes what I got him. I know he will. I get to see him one day earlier than I originally planned (shout out to JT our scheduling man for that one!!) and I simply cannot wait. The two hour drive is gonna be killa this time. Just knowing that Jimmy's at the other end will make me want to be there soooo much more. Gosh. I can't wait.

Ok, so, this entire thing was about Jimmy. I would say "in other news...", but there is no other news. =)
Happy. I love life.

amourtoujours, kait michelle

Addicted to your voice missing you more and more with every second that passes wanting to hold you and tell you how much I love you more and more with every second that passes.

Not much longer now. I love you.

amourtoujours, kait michelle

Listless and restless and sleep deprived of your arms and lips kissing me showing me telling me that I'm yours you're mine always.

Love is on my lips dripping with each word I whisper through the void to your waiting ears.

amourtoujours, kait michelle

Reading books about vampires and fantasizing about the boy who gets my heart going on ten days until I can see that beautiful face in my mind as I read about love and despair and hopelessness and victory and realizing that you're everything that other people see in you that you don't see in yourself and more sighing as the longing grows days on end of summer not wanting to wish it away from your comfort zone that you need that you crave that you miss terribly.

No amount of dreaming can do him justice just to feel his arms around you again and again after a month do you remember what it feels like to be loved so passionately in love with the idea of you whispering in my ear and kissing my neck your neck it's what you love is all you need.

amourtoujours, kait michelle

I'm sitting here loving life.

My vacation with Jimmy and his family was absolutely wonderful. We had so much fun camping with his cousin, Josh. I got to be the photographer for my hott, wetsuit clad wakeboarder and baked a nice, dark tan color in the beautiful sun. I'm so grateful to his parents for taking me - I had such a great time.

My family is going to Myrtle Beach w/ the Ritenours, the other Houcks, and the Schobers August 2nd through the 9th and unfortunately our condo is only big enough for 4 people so there's no way we can take my Jimmy. I'm so upset. =(
Like, I'm really excited for the vacation. I just really, really wish that Jimmy could come with us. It would be so much fun. I love spending time with him and he's never really had a beach vacation before. I'm still working on convincing the parents but I just don't think it's gonna happen.

I just visited Jimmy from Wednesday after I opened until yesterday (Friday) before I had to work. It was seriously so much fun. It had only been like a week since we were separated after vacation but I just hate being away from him for any length of time. We're both poor kids and gas prices are absolutely ridiculous so I think we're gonna be pretty limited in seeing each other before he moves back up here for school. I hate to wish the summer away, but I can't wait until he's living 2 minutes away from me again and I can see him whenever I want. I'm excited to have him, Charlie, and Johnny to play poker and video games and watch movies with again!!

Right now I just finished cleaning my room while watching Live Free or Die Hard (mmm, Bruce Willis) and I'm gonna have to jump in the shower soon to get ready for work. I think I close with Eli and Jen tonight...yay!!

Jimmy's family went to his uncle's camp for the rest of the weekend so I'm not sure how much I'll get to talk to him in the next couple of days. I hope it's more than I'm expecting. Kaity is in looooooove. Totally.

Our one year anniversary is rapidly approaching. On August 21st I will celebrate my first ever one year anniversary. I'm so excited. It's such a huge milestone for us and our relationship and I really feel that we're stronger with every day that passes. I love you Jimmy!! Hopefully we'll be planning out our anniversary soon! I already requested off work so we're good to go!!

Alright, enough randomness for one day. =)

Well, it's been awhile.

I don't know. I just haven't really had the motivation to post lately, I guess.

I seriously can't wait for this school year to be over. I honestly just can't wait to come home and be owned by Starbucks and see Jimmy whenever I possibly can. This year has been the best and the worst in different ways. I'm not going to go through everything right now on here because, honestly, I don't even want people to know some of it. Regardless, I just need to come home. I just need to be at home. There are a lot of things I want to do with this summer and I really hope I can.

Bryce <3

I don't know why this had to happen. I don't understand. I miss you and love you so much. You were one of the best friends I've ever had in my entire life. I can't believe we wasted so much time before actually getting to know each other. I'm so thankful that my Mom randomly met you at the movies and gave you my screen name lol. We had soooo much fun, Bryce. Remember our fort under Leah's bed and how you kicked her head when she tried to come in? My dry-erase board still says, "Bryce & Kait's Fort: No Leah's Allowed!" You made me love The Office and I was so looking forward to applying at Dunder-Mifflin with you someday. What am I going to do without you? Your birthday last year we got you that Spiderman card and Leah and I pretty much ate the entire cake we got for you...thanks for at least pretending to like it!! Remember that night when Leah gave us her camera and we were waiting for Brandon, Bonnie, & Joe to get to IUP and we took a million pictures of us making mean faces and other random things?? We had so much fun, Bryce. So much fun. You were always so happy and so positive...you made me a happy person, too. I don't know what your reasons were...I wish I could have made a difference somehow. I know that it might not have changed anything in the end, but you changed me, Bryce. You made the transition to college so easy for me...You were ALWAYS there. I had so much fun when we went to Monroeville Mall and you took me to your house before taking me home. It was so neat to see all your family's pictures and your collections. Remember that time that we ate at Ruby Tuesday's? Ahhhh I miss you, Bryce! It doesn't seem real yet. When I look at pictures of you and me I just want to send you a text message and tell you I miss you. I just want to get the random "hey guys lets go to Macys" text messages. I loved those, you know. You always made me laugh. You always made me smile. I'll always love and miss you, buddy.
"Spiderman, spiderman..." --- "No, Bryce! Stop! You'll get it stuck in my head again!"

I LOVE YOU BRYCE! REST IN PEACE <3

amourtoujours, kait michelle

Ugh. I only have like two weeks left before I'll be sitting in the classrooms of IUP again. How crazy is that? Don't get me wrong, I'm beyond excited to move into the apartment with Leeyuh and Chrystuh...but can't we just live there and not go to school? That would be ideal.

I'm such a lazy kid and haven't updated this thing in so long that I wouldn't really know where to start and not leave out 4 million important things, so I'm not even going to try. Most recently, though I went to Kennywood with some awesome Starbucks kids!! (Jim, Kate, Mary, Eli, CJ, Kasie, & Sally!) We seriously had so much fun. Jim made me ride every single scary ride...everyone should be proud that I'm alive. I know I am. So besides riding scary rides, I seriously had so much fun. I love the fact that I have such an awesome group of friends from work...I'm pretty sure that not everyone can say they want to spend a day at Kennywood with the people they work with.
